lettered tasks per queue\n- Independent DLQ per named queue\n\n**Phase 7: Task Dependencies** (8 tests, 8 points)\n- Tasks can declare dependencies on other task IDs\n- Blocked tasks unavailable until dependencies complete\n- Auto-unblock when dependency completes\n- Detect and reject circular dependencies at creation time\n- Error on non-existent dependencies\n- Failed dependency doesn't fail dependents (stays blocked)\n- Inspect task dependency status\n\n**Phase 8: Concurrency Control** (7 tests, 7 points)\n- Per-queue max concurrent processing limit\n- If limit reached, dequeue returns null\n- Completing/failing task frees concurrency slot\n- Default: unlimited (no limit)\n- Query concurrency limit and active count\n- Respects priority ordering within limits\n\n**Phase 9: Progress Tracking & Cancellation** (8 tests, 8 points)\n- Processing tasks report progress (0-100%) with optional message\n- Query task's current progress\n- Subscribe to progress updates (listeners)\n- Unsubscribe from progress updates\n- Cancel pending tasks (removed from queue)\n- Cancel processing tasks (status updated)\n- Cancelled tasks never retry\n\n**Phase 10: Recurring Tasks (Cron-like)** (7 tests, 7 points)\n- Schedules associate cron expression + queue + task template\n- Simple cron subset:\n  - `*/N * * * *` - every N minutes\n  - `0 * * * *` - every hour on the hour\n  - `0 0 * * *` - every day at midnight\n- Create, remove, list schedules\n- Manual \"tick\" mechanism to evaluate and enqueue due tasks\n- Enqueued recurring tasks follow all queue rules\n- Removing schedule stops future occurrences\n\n**Phase 11: Middleware Pipeline** (7 tests, 7 points)\n- Register middleware per queue\n- Middleware receives task + \"next\" function\n- Not calling \"next\" skips task processing\n- Middleware can modify task\n- Middleware errors mark task as failed\n- Processing handler/function per queue (runs after middleware)\n- Independent middleware stack per queue\n\n**Phase 12: Graceful Shutdo