+# Task Queue System Design
+
+## Architecture
+
+Single `TaskQueue` class exported from `src/index.ts` as the main API surface.
+Internally composed of per-queue `QueueBucket` instances stored in a `Map<string, QueueBucket>`.
+
+### Task Model
+
+```typescript
+interface Task<T = unknown> {
+  id: string;                    // UUID
+  payload: T;                    // User data
+  status: TaskStatus;            // pending | processing | completed | failed | cancelled
+  createdAt: Date;               // Creation timestamp
+  priority: number;              // 1-10, default 5
+  queue: string;                 // Queue name
+  delay?: number;                // Delay in ms
+  runAt?: Date;                  // Absolute availability time
+  availableAt: Date;             // Computed: createdAt + delay or runAt or createdAt
+  attempts: number;              // Current attempt count
+  maxRetries: number;            // Max retries, default 3
+  backoffDelay: number;          // Base backoff delay, default 1000ms
+  error?: string;                // Last error
+  dependencies: string[];        // Task IDs this depends on
+  progress: number;              // 0-100
+  progressMessage?: string;      // Optional progress message
+}
+```
+
+### QueueBucket (Internal)
+
+Per-queue state container:
+- `pending: Task[]` - sorted by availability, priority, FIFO
+- `processing: Map<string, Task>` - currently active tasks
+- `dlq: Task[]` - dead-lettered tasks
+- `middleware: MiddlewareFn[]` - middleware stack
+- `handler?: ProcessorFn` - task processor
+- `concurrencyLimit: number` - 0 = unlimited
+- `activeCount: number` - current processing count
+
+### Key Methods
+
+Phase 1-2: `enqueue(payload, options?)`, `dequeue(queue?)`, `size(queue?)`
+Phase 3: Priority in options
+Phase 4: `delay`/`runAt` in options
+Phase 5: `complete(taskId)`, `fail(taskId, error?)`
+Phase 6: `getDeadLetterTasks(queue)`, `retryDeadLetter(taskId)`, `clearDeadLetterQueue(queue)`
+Phase 7: `dependencies` in options, dependency resolution
+Phase 8: `setConcurrency(queue, limit)`, `getConcurrency(queue)`
+Phase 9: `updateProgress(taskId, pct, msg?)`, `onProgress(taskId, cb)`, `offProgress(taskId, cb)`, `cancel(taskId)`
+Phase 10: `addSchedule(id, cron, queue, payload)`, `removeSchedule(id)`, `listSchedules()`, `tick(now?)`
+Phase 11: `use(queue, middleware)`, `process(queue, handler)`
+Phase 12: `shutdown(options?)` returns Promise<ShutdownResult>
+
+### File Structure
+
+- `src/index.ts` - exports TaskQueue class and types
+- `src/TaskQueue.ts` - main class
+- `src/QueueBucket.ts` - per-queue state
+- `src/Task.ts` - task interface and factory
+- `src/types.ts` - shared types
+- `src/cron.ts` - simple cron parser
+- `src/utils.ts` - UUID generation, etc.
